Message: 1
Date: Fri, 16 Jul 2010 11:57:35 -0400
From: "Nicholas J. Kuhn" <njk4x@virginia.edu>
Subject: [ALGTOP-L] More on McCord's construction
To: algtop-l@lists.lehigh.edu
Message-ID: <web-9111064@neon.mail.virginia.edu>
Content-Type: text/plain;charset=iso-8859-1;format="flowed"

Since there seems to be some interest in these models for K(A,n)'s, 
here is a little more info about McCord's construction B(A,X), where A 
is an abelian topological monoid, and X is a based space.

1. B(A,X) is again an abelian topological monoid, and an abelian 
topological group if A was.

2. with N = the natural numbers. B(N,X) = SP^infty(X).

3. With A = a discrete abelian group, B(A,S^n) = K(A,n).

4. The category of abelian topological monoids is tensored over based 
spaces, and B(A,X) = X tensor A.

5. Since S^n = S^1 smash S^1 ... smash S^1, one sees that B(A,S^n) IS 
obtained from iterating the `bar construction' B(_,S^1).  But writing 
it as B(A,S^n) reveals much more symmetry, e.g. a natural action of 
the monoid Omega^nS^n.

6. There is an evident filtration on B(A,X) that leads to 
configuration spaces and stuff.

As a reference for this, besides McCord's own paper, see my paper: 
 Kuhn, Nicholas J. The McCord model for the tensor product of a space 
and a commutative ring spectrum.  Categorical decomposition techniques 
in algebraic topology (Isle of Skye, 2001),  213--236, Progr. Math., 
215, Birkh?user, Basel, 2004.  I also consider allowing A to be things 
like commutative S-algebras.

------------------------------

